[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_swppq")
reagent_id = "SO2"
title = "Sulfur Dioxide "
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]SO₂[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]64 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]Gas[/cell]
[cell]Color:[/cell][cell]Colorless[/cell]
[cell]Smell:[/cell][cell]Sharp, irritating odor[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reaction[/b]
S + O₂ → SO₂
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Toxic gas that irritates the eyes and lungs.
• Dissolves in water to form sulfurous acid (H₂SO₃).
• Formed when sulfur burns in oxygen.
[b]Where sulfur dioxide is found[/b]
• Produced by volcanoes.
• Released when coal or oil containing sulfur burns.
• Present in some industrial emissions.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Production of sulfuric acid (H₂SO₄).
• Used as a preservative in some foods.
• Used for bleaching and disinfecting.
[b]Safety[/b]
Harmful to breathe and can cause respiratory problems.
Contributes to acid rain."
